    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>By Mr. ROSS:H.R. 243.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8: ``The Congress shall have power tolay and collect taxes, duties, imposts and excises, to paythe debts and provide for the common defense and generalwelfare of the United States; but all duties, imposts andexcises shall be uniform throughout the United States.''[Page H86]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
